metadata.name: Keyed Doorway #19
metadata.description:
"Keyed Doorway" represents a threshold between our world and a world beyond our own, accessible only through mastery of a complex combination of lines and shapes. 

The intricate arrangements of lines and shapes serve as a metaphor for the challenges and obstacles that must be overcome in order to reach the other side, symbolizing the idea that we are always capable of unlocking new worlds through our own personal growth and mastery of new skills. 

The "Keyed Doorway" invites the viewer to imagine the possibilities beyond their current understanding and to dream about what lies beyond. It is a representation of the endless potential of the human spirit and the journey towards discovery and exploration.

- hit 's' to save .svg
- hit 'p' to save .png

metadata.name: Incomlete #126
metadata.description:
Incomplete is normal while complete is unnormal.
Each artwork has one status: Normal, Complete, or Rare.

Even you can pause or rewind the process, you still can't change the incomplete result.
Learn to enjoy the incomplete is the only way. 
Just like your life.

The blocks will move and combine. We could have multiple point of view for the incomplete:
4 different Types according to the distance.
3 level of Stroke for different style.
3 types of Shadow and light.
2 different Materials of blocks.
And 40 selected color Palettes with different amount and angle of blocks

[Interact]
[p] Pause 
[r] Rewind 
[s] Save in PNG 

Made with p5.js

metadata.name: The Fringe #96
metadata.description:
We are innately aware of our bodies' position through perception of space. If we are visibly surrounded by walls with flooring under, a ceiling above, and a window facing the sky, we know we are inside of an enclosed space, with a view of outside. But how does a room stopped being an enclosed space? Can a space with 3 walls be considered a room? If we are surrounded by walls but our ceiling is gone, then are we inside or outside? This is an exploration on the edges of our ability to perceive space. The fringes that instill some fear in our mind. And that fear is failing to make sense of our position in a space that slowly loses its tangibility.

------------
Press [s] to save captured image
------------
It may take a few seconds to render, depending on the device.

created using WEBGL on p5.js
